-- Blockbuster reports wider loss
-- 
-- Wed May 2, 2007 8:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/02/us-blockbuster-results-idUSWEN750520070502

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Blockbuster Inc BBI.N, the nation's No. 1 video rental chain, on Wednesday reported a deeper first quarter net loss on costs associated with its new online rental program and flat in-store rental revenue. 

 Blockbuster reported a net loss of $46.4 million, or 26 cents per share, compared with a net loss of $1.9 million, or 3 cents per share in last year's first quarter.